women's_national_soccer_team\"}, {\"begin\": 1612, \"end\": 1615, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anterior_cruciate_ligament\", \"score\": 0.9430036116759827, \"rank\": 0.06044132558800746, \"text\": \"ACL\", \"types\": [\"Q4936952\", \"Q39888\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anterior_cruciate_ligament\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anterior_cruciate_ligament\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"However, it may take even longer for professional athletes as doctors are cautious and prefer the injury to be completely healed before making a return to competition.\", \"from\": 1700, \"to\": 1867, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"A timeframe is too early to be determined for Kerr.\", \"from\": 1869, \"to\": 1920, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The forward had recently suffered a calf injury and missed out on the first two games of the 2023 Women's World Cup, before returning in fine form to take Australia into the semi-finals which was watched by 11.5 million viewers in the country at its peak.\", \"from\": 1922, \"to\": 2177, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2077, \"end\": 2086, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_women's_national_soccer_team\", \"score\": 0.9999965671256438, \"rank\": 2.04256536290433e-06, \"text\": \"Australia\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_women's_national_soccer_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_women's_national_soccer_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Australia is set to play a two-legged Olympic qualifying play-offs against Uzbekistan away on February 24 and then at Marvel Stadium in Melbourne on February 28.\", \"from\": 2179, \"to\": 2340, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2179, \"end\": 2188, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_women's_national_soccer_team\", \"score\": 0.9999965671256438, \"rank\": 2.04256536290433e-06, \"text\": \"Australia\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wik